def preproccessing_and_aggregation_data(file, REGIONS, NY_LOCATION):


  data = pd.read_csv(file, parse_dates=['tpep_pickup_datetime', 'tpep_dropoff_datetime'])

  #     
  data = data[data['tpep_dropoff_datetime'] != data['tpep_pickup_datetime']]

  #      
  data = data[data.passenger_count != 0]

  #      
  data = data[data.trip_distance != 0]

  #       -
  data = data[((data.pickup_longitude > NY_LOCATION[0]) & (data.pickup_longitude < NY_LOCATION[1])) & ((data.pickup_latitude > NY_LOCATION[2]) & (data.pickup_latitude < NY_LOCATION[3]))]

  #    
  data['tpep_pickup_hour'] = data.tpep_pickup_datetime.map(lambda x: x.floor(freq='h'))

  #        (  )
  statistic = binned_statistic_2d(data['pickup_longitude'].values, 
                                  data['pickup_latitude'].values, 
                                  data['VendorID'], 
                                  statistic='count', 
                                  bins=[REGIONS['west'].append(REGIONS['east']).unique(), 
                                        REGIONS['south'].append(REGIONS['north']).unique()], 
                                  expand_binnumbers=True)
                                    
  data['region'] = (statistic[3][0] - 1) * 50 + statistic[3][1]

  #       ,      ,       
  agg_table = pd.pivot_table(data, values='VendorID', index='tpep_pickup_hour', columns='region', aggfunc='count')
  data = None
  return agg_table

def load_data(AGG_FILES, date_before, date_after):
  data = pd.concat([pd.read_csv(file, sep=';', parse_dates=['tpep_pickup_hour']) for file in AGG_FILES])
  data.set_index('tpep_pickup_hour', inplace=True)
  data = data[COLUMNS_FROM_2_WEEK]
  data = data[date_after <= data.index]
  data = data[data.index <= date_before]
  data.fillna(value=0, inplace=True)
  return data



def get_regions_from_second_week():
  data = pd.read_csv('agg_yellow_tripdata_2016-05.csv', sep=';')
  data.set_index('tpep_pickup_hour', inplace=True)
  cols = (data.sum(axis=0) / len(data)) >= 5
  cols = cols.reset_index()
  return cols[cols[0] == True]['index'].values

def my_style_function(x):
    color = ''
    if x['properties']['cluster'] == 0:
        color = 'green'
    elif x['properties']['cluster'] == 1:
        color = 'orange'
    elif x['properties']['cluster'] == 2:
        color = 'blue'
    elif x['properties']['cluster'] == 3:
        color = 'green'
    elif x['properties']['cluster'] == 4:
        color = 'yellow'
    return {'fillColor': color, 'stroke': True, 'weight': 0.5, 'fillOpacity':0.7}


def add_features(data, k, holidays):
    data['const'] = 1
    data['lin'] = np.arange(1, data.shape[0]+1)
    data['is_holiday'] = [x in holidays for x in data.index.floor('d')]
    features_columns = ['const', 'lin', 'is_holiday']
    features_columns += month_features(data)
    features_columns += weekday_features(data)
    features_columns += hour_features(data)
    for i in range(1, k+1):
        week_sin_col = f'week_sin_{i}'
        week_cos_col = f'week_cos_{i}'
        data[week_sin_col] = np.sin(np.array(data['lin'] * 2 * np.pi * i / 168))
        data[week_cos_col] = np.cos(np.array(data['lin'] * 2 * np.pi * i / 168))
        features_columns += [week_sin_col, week_cos_col]

    data.replace(True, 1, inplace=True)
    data.replace(False, 0, inplace=True)
    return features_columns

def get_reg_pred(data, features_columns):
    train_data = np.array(data[features_columns])
    train_labels = np.array(data['trips'])
    
    model = ElasticNet(random_state=42)
    model.fit(train_data, train_labels)
    
    preds = model.predict(data[features_columns])
    
    data['reg_pred'] = preds
    data['reg_resid'] = data['trips'] - preds
    
    return preds

def month_features(data):
  features_columns = []
  for x in range(1, 13):
    col_name = f'month{x}'
    data[col_name] = [data.index.month == x][0]
    features_columns.append(col_name)
  
  data.replace(True, 1, inplace=True)
  data.replace(False, 0, inplace=True)
  return features_columns

def hour_features(data):
  features_columns = []
  for x in range(0, 24):
    col_name = f'hour{x}'
    data[col_name] = [data.index.hour == x][0]
    features_columns.append(col_name)
  data.replace(True, 1, inplace=True)
  data.replace(False, 0, inplace=True)
  return features_columns

def weekday_features(data):
  features_columns = []
  for x in range(0, 7):
    col_name = f'weekday{x}'
    data[col_name] = [data.index.weekday == x][0]
    features_columns.append(col_name)
  data.replace(True, 1, inplace=True)
  data.replace(False, 0, inplace=True)
  return features_columns

def plot_linear_reg(data_cluster):
  plt.figure(figsize=(20, 5))
  data_cluster['trips'].rolling(24).mean().plot(legend=True, title=f'  +     K={K}')
  data_cluster['reg_pred'].rolling(24).mean().plot(legend=True)
  plt.show()

  plt.figure(figsize=(20, 5))
  data_cluster.reg_resid.rolling(24).mean().plot(title='', legend=True)
  plt.show()

def plot_decompose(data_cluster, reg_resid):
  result = sm.tsa.seasonal_decompose(data_cluster[reg_resid].dropna(), freq=24)
  fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=4, ncols=1, figsize=(25,10))
  axes[0].plot(result.observed)
  axes[0].set(ylabel='Observed')
  axes[1].plot(result.trend)
  axes[1].set(ylabel='trend')
  axes[2].plot(result.seasonal)
  axes[2].set(ylabel='seasonal')
  axes[3].plot(result.resid)  
  axes[3].set(ylabel='resid') 
  print(" -: p=%f" % sm.tsa.stattools.adfuller(data_cluster.trips)[1])
  plt.show()

def plot_acf_pacf(data_cluster):
  print('    ')
  plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
  ax = plt.subplot(211)
  sm.graphics.tsa.plot_acf(data_cluster.reg_resid_diff.dropna().values.squeeze(), lags=168, ax=ax)
  ax = plt.subplot(212)
  sm.graphics.tsa.plot_pacf(data_cluster.reg_resid_diff.dropna().values.squeeze(), lags=168, ax=ax)
  plt.show()



def select_best_arima(data, params, d, D):
  results = []
  best_aic = float("inf")
  warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')
  i=0
  for param in params:
      print(i, '-', param, '...', datetime.datetime.now(), '...')
      i+=1
      #try except ,         
      try:
          model=sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(data.reg_resid, order=(param[0], d, param[1]), 
                                          seasonal_order=(param[2], D, param[3], 24)).fit(disp=-1, maxiter=14)
      
      # ,          
      except ValueError:
          print('wrong parameters:', param)
          continue
      aic = model.aic
      #  , aic, 
      if aic < best_aic:
          best_model = model
          best_aic = aic
          best_param = param
      results.append([param, model.aic])
      
  warnings.filterwarnings('default')
  return (best_model, results)

model = KMeans(n_clusters=4, random_state=42)
predictions = model.fit_predict(data.T)

fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(15, 10))
vals = np.array(data).T

obs = [SparseRandomProjection(2, random_state=42), 
       PCA(2, random_state=42), 
       TruncatedSVD(2, random_state=42), 
       TSNE(2, perplexity=23, learning_rate=200, random_state=42), 
       MDS(2, random_state=42)]
titles = ['Random projection', 'PCA', 'TruncatedSVD', 'TSNE', 'MDS']
for i in range(len(obs)):
    points = obs[i].fit_transform(vals)
    ax = axs[i%2, i%3]
    ax.scatter([j[0] for j in points], [j[1] for j in points], c=predictions)
    ax.set_title(titles[i])
mds_model = MDS(n_components=2, dissimilarity='precomputed')
points = mds_model.fit_transform(pairwise_distances(vals, metric='cosine'))
ax = axs[-1, -1]
ax.scatter([j[0] for j in points], [j[1] for j in points], c=predictions)
ax.set_title('MDS cosine')

Делаем динамический прогноз на 6 часов вперед для каждого часа мая 2016¶

Попробуем вначале на одном регионе в кластере №0¶
In [ ]:
%%time
END_APRIL = datetime.datetime(2016, 4, 30, 23)
CUMULATIVE_ERROR = 0
K = 200
#     2016
data = load_data(AGG_FILES, 
                 date_after=datetime.datetime(2015, 12, 1, 0), 
                 date_before=datetime.datetime(2016, 5, 31, 23)) 
data = pd.DataFrame(data['1233']) #  1233 
data.columns = ['trips']
features_columns = add_features(data, K, HOLIDAYS)

#         2016
train_data = np.array(data[features_columns].loc[:END_APRIL])
train_y = np.array(data['trips'].loc[:END_APRIL])
model_reg = ElasticNet(random_state=42)
model_reg.fit(train_data, train_y)

#          dataframe
preds = model_reg.predict(data[features_columns])
data['reg_pred'] = preds
data['reg_resid'] = data['trips'] - preds

#  SARIMAX     2016    

model_res = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(data.reg_resid.loc[:END_APRIL], 
                                      order=(2, 1, 1),
                                      seasonal_order=(1, 1, 1, 24)).fit(disp=False, maxiter=50)

#model_res = load('model_0.joblib')

#     .filter  
model_fitted = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(data.reg_resid, 
                                         order=(2, 1, 1),
                                         seasonal_order=(1, 1, 1, 24)
                                         ).filter(model_res.params)


#       
start = END_APRIL + datetime.timedelta(hours=1)
predictions_reg_arima = pd.DataFrame(index=pd.date_range(start=datetime.datetime(2016, 5, 1), 
                                                         end=datetime.datetime(2016, 5, 31, 23), 
                                                         freq='H'), 
                                     columns=['pred'])
for i in range(739): #   739 
  #       
  end = start + datetime.timedelta(hours=5)
  
  #       ARIMA  6  
  predictions = data.reg_pred.loc[start:end] + model_fitted.predict(start=start, end=end, dynamic=True)
  predictions_reg_arima['pred'].loc[start:end] = predictions

  #    
  trips = data.trips.loc[start:end]

  #  
  CUMULATIVE_ERROR += abs(trips - predictions).sum()

  #        
  start = start + datetime.timedelta(hours=1)
In [ ]:
print(CUMULATIVE_ERROR / (6*739))
plt.figure(figsize=(25,5))
predictions_reg_arima.pred.plot()
data.trips.loc[END_APRIL:].plot()
data.reg_pred.loc[END_APRIL:].plot()
plt.legend()
plt.show()

%%time
END_APRIL = datetime.datetime(2016, 4, 30, 23)
CUMULATIVE_ERROR = 0
HOLIDAYS = USFederalHolidayCalendar().holidays(start=datetime.datetime(2015, 12, 1), end=datetime.datetime(2016, 6, 1))
K = 200
params = {0: [2, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 24],
          1: [2, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 24],
          2: [2, 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 24],
          3: [1, 1, 1, 2, 1, 1, 24]}


for i in range(len(regions)): #   102  (     )
  #  
  region_num = str(regions.iloc[i].name)
  cluster_num = int(regions.iloc[i].cluster)
  param = params.get(cluster_num)
  cumulative_error = 0

  #     
  data = load_data(AGG_FILES, 
                  date_after=datetime.datetime(2015, 12, 1, 0), 
                  date_before=datetime.datetime(2016, 5, 31, 23)) 
  data = pd.DataFrame(data[region_num])
  data.columns = ['trips']
  features_columns = add_features(data, K, HOLIDAYS)

  #         2016
  train_data = np.array(data[features_columns].loc[:END_APRIL])
  train_y = np.array(data['trips'].loc[:END_APRIL])
  model_reg = ElasticNet(random_state=42)
  model_reg.fit(train_data, train_y)

  #          dataframe
  preds = model_reg.predict(data[features_columns])
  data['reg_pred'] = preds
  data['reg_resid'] = data['trips'] - preds

  #  SARIMAX     2016    
  model_res = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(data.reg_resid.loc[:END_APRIL], 
                                        order=(param[0], param[1], param[2]),
                                        seasonal_order=(param[3], param[4], param[5], param[6])
                                        ).fit(disp=False, maxiter=15)

  #     .filter  
  model_fitted = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(data.reg_resid, 
                                          order=(param[0], param[1], param[2]),
                                          seasonal_order=(param[3], param[4], param[5], param[6])
                                          ).filter(model_res.params)


  #       
  start = END_APRIL + datetime.timedelta(hours=1)

  for _ in range(739): #   739   30.04.2016 23:00  31.05.2021 17:00
    #       
    end = start + datetime.timedelta(hours=5)
    
    #       ARIMA  6  
    predictions = data.reg_pred.loc[start:end] + model_fitted.predict(start=start, end=end, dynamic=True)

    #    
    trips = data.trips.loc[start:end]

    #  
    cumulative_error += abs(trips - predictions).sum()

    #   
    start = start + datetime.timedelta(hours=1)
  print(f'i: {i}, : {cluster_num}, : {region_num}, : {cumulative_error / (6 * 739)}')
  CUMULATIVE_ERROR += cumulative_error

Создаем файл с результатом для kaggle¶

%%time
END_APRIL = datetime.datetime(2016, 4, 30, 23)
END_MAY = datetime.datetime(2016, 5, 31, 23)
CUMULATIVE_ERROR = 0
HOLIDAYS = USFederalHolidayCalendar().holidays(start=datetime.datetime(2015, 12, 1), end=datetime.datetime(2016, 7, 1))
K = 200
PARAMS = {0: [2, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 24],
          1: [2, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 24],
          2: [2, 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 24],
          3: [1, 1, 1, 2, 1, 1, 24]}

"""
    kaggle     
with open('kaggle_answer.csv', 'w') as file:
  csv.writer(file).writerow(['id', 'y'])
"""

for i in range(len(regions)):
  #  
  region_num = str(regions.iloc[i].name)
  cluster_num = int(regions.iloc[i].cluster)
  param = PARAMS.get(cluster_num)
  cumulative_error = 0
  
  #     
  data = load_data(AGG_FILES, 
                  date_after=datetime.datetime(2015, 12, 1, 0), 
                  date_before=datetime.datetime(2016, 6, 30, 23)) 
  data = pd.DataFrame(data[region_num])
  data.columns = ['trips']
  features_columns = add_features(data, K, HOLIDAYS)

  #         2016
  train_data = np.array(data[features_columns].loc[:END_MAY])
  train_y = np.array(data['trips'].loc[:END_MAY])
  model_reg = ElasticNet(random_state=42)
  model_reg.fit(train_data, train_y)

  #          dataframe
  preds = model_reg.predict(data[features_columns])
  data['reg_pred'] = preds
  data['reg_resid'] = data['trips'] - preds

  #  SARIMAX     2016    

  model_res = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(data.reg_resid.loc[:END_MAY], 
                                        order=(param[0], param[1], param[2]),
                                        seasonal_order=(param[3], param[4], param[5], param[6])
                                        ).fit(disp=False, maxiter=15)
  #     .filter  
  model_fitted = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(data.reg_resid, 
                                          order=(param[0], param[1], param[2]),
                                          seasonal_order=(param[3], param[4], param[5], param[6])
                                          ).filter(model_res.params)

  #       
  start = END_MAY + datetime.timedelta(hours=1)
  kaggle_answer = []
  for _ in range(715): #   715   31.05.2016 23:00  30.06.2021 17:00
    #       
    end = start + datetime.timedelta(hours=5)
    
    #       ARIMA  6  
    predictions = data.reg_pred.loc[start:end] + model_fitted.predict(start=start, end=end, dynamic=True)

    #    
    trips = data.trips.loc[start:end]

    #  
    cumulative_error += abs(trips - predictions).sum()
    
    #        kaggle   
    kagle_id = start - datetime.timedelta(hours=1)
    for predict in zip(predictions, range(1,7)):
      kaggle_answer.append([region_num+'_'+str(kagle_id.strftime('%Y-%m-%d'))+'_'+str(kagle_id.hour)+'_'+str(predict[1]), str(int(round(predict[0], 0)))])
    
    #      
    start = start + datetime.timedelta(hours=1)

  #        kaggle
  pd.DataFrame(kaggle_answer, columns=['id', 'y']).to_csv('kaggle_answer.csv', mode='a', index=False, header=False)
